'''Eugene Kormendi''' (1889–1959)<ref>http://americanart.si.edu/collections/search/artist/?id=2693</ref> was a Hungarian sculptor. He studied at the [[Academy of Budapest]] before moving to Paris to collaborate with [[Auguste Rodin]] and [[Jean Paul Lorenz]]. Kormendi first came to the United States in 1939 along with his wife, Elizabeth, to attend the New York World's fair.
