{{Infobox Museum |name=Romanian Academy in Rome |image=Q03 - Accademia di Romania P1010352.JPG |caption= |map_type= |map_caption= |latitude= |longitude= |established=1920 |dissolved= |location=[[Rome]], [[Italy]] |type=[[Research center]] |visitors = |director= |curator= |publictransit= |website=[http://www.accadromania.it/ '''Official website'''] }}
The '''Romanian Academy in Rome''' ({{lang-ro|Școala română din Roma}}, {{lang-it|Accademia di Romania in Roma}}) is a research institution under the aegis of the [[Romanian Academy]], founded in 1920 by an initiative of archaeologist [[Vasile Pârvan]] and historian [[Nicolae Iorga]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accadromania.it/accademia.htm |title=Accademia di Romania in Roma — chi siamo? |publisher=Accademia di Romania in Roma |accessdate=2016-10-28}}</ref> The site of the Romanian Academy in Rome is on the [[Pincio]] (Pincian Hill), near the [[Villa Borghese gardens]], in [[Rome]], [[Italy]]. The villa housing the Romanian Academy in Rome dates from 1933 and was designed by [[Petre Antonescu]].
