{{Infobox journal | title = Yearbook for Traditional Music | cover = | former_name = Journal of the International Folk Music Council | abbreviation = Yearb. Tradit. Music | discipline = [[Traditional music]] | editor = Kati Szego | publisher = International Council for Traditional Music | country = | history = 1949-present | frequency = Annual | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSN = 0740-1558 | eISSN = 2304-3857 | CODEN = | JSTOR = 07401558 | LCCN = 82647116 | OCLC = 960771625 | website = http://www.ictmusic.org/publications/yearbook-for-traditional-music | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> }} The '''''Yearbook for Traditional Music''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering research on [[folk music]] and [[folk dance|dance]]. It is published by the [[International Council for Traditional Music]], once a year in December. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Kati Szego. The ''Yearbook'' was established in 1949 as the '''''Journal of the International Folk Music Council''''', obtaining its current title in 1981. The journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[Arts & Humanities Citation Index]] and [[Current Contents]]/Arts & Humanities.<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2014-10-08}}</ref>
